We’re back with more sustainability stories! 

@tesweens heads to Chamonix to uncover Salomon’s new sustainability commitments designed to improve our in-person events' carbon footprint in order to reduce the environmental impact of our athletes and ambassadors. 

      As always, Tim is joined by an all-star cast. This time, Salomon athletes Emelie Forsberg, Leah Evans, and Stan Rey stop by to explain what athletes are doing to lessen their environmental impact. ♲

      Plus, Salomon sports marketing manager Bruno Laroque explains the reason behind these new sports marketing goals and Magali Chevalier from Marathon du Mont Blanc lets us behind the scenes to see how the race has improved its environmental impact in recent years. 🙌

We are excited to share with you a new web series where our Global Communications Manager, @tesweens, takes us behind the scenes of our journey to becoming more sustainable. 🏔

First up, Tim tells us more about the improvements we've made in our winter sports products. From saving 5.4 tons of plastic from hitting landfills each year to the development of the  S/MAX eSkin Nordic ski, our first ski constructed with a sustainable mindset, Salomon is on the right track (pun intended). 🎿

Stay tuned for more from Tim and our sustainability crew. #PlayMinded #TimeToPlay

Stay tuned, full film coming on Salomon TV this November. #followtheforecast #TimeToPlay
